Description: The 'type' of alias
This persons usual DHB (District Health Board)
Administrative Gender - the gender that the person is considered to have for administration and record keeping purposes.
Administrative Gender - the gender that the patient is considered to have for administration and record keeping purposes.
Collection of specialties handled by the service site. This is more of a medical term.
Specific specialty of the practitioner.
Identifies what kind of team.  This is to support differentiation between multiple co-existing teams- such as care plan team- episode of care team- longitudinal care team.
Indicates the current state of the care team.
A language the practitioner is able to use in patient communication.
Physical form of the location- e.g. building- room- vehicle- road.
The status property covers the general availability of the resource- not the current value which may be covered by the operationStatus- or by a schedule/slots if they are configured for the location.
The kind(s) of organization that this is.
Indicates specific responsibility of an individual within the care team- such as "Primary care physician"- "Trained social worker counselor"- "Caregiver"- etc.
Roles which this practitioner is authorized to perform for the organization.
Identifies the broad category of service being performed or delivered.
Coded representation of the qualification.
Indicates the type of function performed at the location.
The current citizenship status
The ethnicity of the patient. Has 4 levels of detail.
The type of extension - eg limited prescribing
The type of condition
The type of service - eg 'DENT' for dental
Current status of the registration
The source of the date of birth - eg from a birth certificate or a passport
The source of information concerning the country of birth
Who stated the patient was deceased
Where the name comes from
The source of the information

No description
